message.content: {"id": "13269", "title": "Incorrect operation order in jarpackager", "description": "The jarpackager operates in the incorrect order. This issue also applies to the '.jardesc' file. It would be better to display a warning in the wizard's header (in addition to the icon) for the '.jardesc' file instead of a dialog box at the end. If the user wants to override this behavior, they should choose the 'save the manifest in the workspace' option along with the 'reuse and save the manifest in the workspace' option. This bug was reported on 20020409 by JRT.", "OB": "The jar file is being created before the overwrite verifications take place. It's worth noting that the message 'saving manifest file failed' is incorrect in this case, as the user has chosen not to overwrite the manifest file (so it is not actually a failure).", "EB": "Regardless, not overwriting this file should not prevent the wizard from completing its operation. The 'use existing manifest from workspace' option should not save a new manifest file.", "SR": ""}
